Tag a person you wanna go on rides with! ☺️

Storytime: 🏍️
Funny how one person can change everything! 

I used to be an indoor girl, scared of bikes and convinced they were dangerous—probably because I’d never even sat on one.
Then came this Guy,💕
A boy with a dream, a bike, and a heart full of adventure.
He took me on my first short ride (with a helmet, of course), and slowly, we went farther… and so did my comfort zone 🥹

He got me riding gear, made safety a priority, and gave me a new kind of freedom I never knew I needed 🫠

Now? I love exploring new places with him on two wheels ✨
Cars still make me sick—but bikes? Bikes feel like freedom 🙂‍↔️
And maybe, just maybe… I’ll be riding one myself someday 😝🙈

Read Caption for details ✨ #healthyliving 

1. Ginger & Lemon Water 🍋🫚
I kickstart my morning with ginger & lemon water. 
• Boosts digestion
• Detoxifies the body
• Strengthens immunity
• Enhances skin health

2. Home Workout 🧘🏽‍♀️
Fitness is a lifestyle, not a strict routine. I may not always be consistent, but staying active most days keeps my body fresh and my mind happy and clear! 💪🏽

3. Healthy Breakfast 🥣
My go-to breakfast is simple: oats with whatever fruits I have at home (usually bananas) and some nuts. Not into oatmeal? Try oats chilla, oats dosa, or an egg sandwich! Want the recipe? Comment “recipe” and I’ll DM it to you! 🥞🍳🥪

4. New Habit: Reading 📖 
I’ve recently started incorporating reading into my mornings. It clears my mind, boosts focus, and sets a calm tone for the day. Slowly, it’s becoming a habit I love! 📚

5. Skincare Talk 🫧
I stick to natural skincare—mostly homemade and Ayurvedic ingredients. My weekly go-to is a rice powder, honey, lemon, and water mask. Simple, refreshing, and chemical-free! 🥰
